title: For Sale:  Rare British Colt 1911 .455 Webley Auto & Ammo
postcontent: Near excellent example of a WWI Colt 1911 chambered in .455 Auto...this pistol was one of only 17,500 manufactured under contract with the British government from 1912 through 1919, with half of those chambered in .45 Acp. One of very few pistols ever chambered in .455 Webley, this pistol would have been issued to the Royal Navy, Royal Flying Corps, or Royal Horse Artillery during the First World War, and likely issued to the RAF for the Second. A mid-production pistol, this gun is estimated to have been manufactured in 1914 or 1915, and would have shipped to the UK Purchasing Commission via the London Armory to be inspected at RSAF Enfield and issued to the British military. Its military service is confirmed by British property markings on the slide, frame and barrel, and the gun presumably remained in service until after the Korean War, judging by the BNP proofing on the barrel. The pistol is accompanied by very scarce .455 Webley Auto cartridges, with three loose rounds and one seven-round unopened pack of WWI vintage. A likely veteran of three wars, this unaltered, non import-marked a near excellent .455 Colt is an important piece of history and suitable for the museum or advanced private collection. Condition is near excellent with the pistol retaining better than 90% high-polish blue finish. There is no rust or deep pitting apart from two patches on the right of the frame.
